DOS-PORT (patch 0085, Phase 9 wave 17.6).

Both wave 17.4 (per-rect partial flush) and wave 17.5 (bbox partial
flush) regressed on real HW:
- Wave 17.4 PLAY1: -7.1 fps title (18.5 vs 25.6 wave-17.3 baseline)
- Wave 17.5 PLAY1: -7.4 fps title (18.3 vs 25.7 wave-17.3 baseline)

Effective bandwidth measurement: full flush 4.4 MB/s, partial 1.07 MB/s
— partial path runs ~4× slower per byte than full flush regardless of
rect-vs-bbox structure. There's an unmodeled cost in SDL3-DOS's
per-rect dosmemput dispatch (or our diff CPU). Bytes-saved-via-
partial-flush math was correct; cost-per-byte at the partial-path was
the missing term.

Postmortem at memory/wave_17_4_partial_flush_regression.md.

This patch keeps the entire wave-17.4 / 17.5 mechanism in tree (the
prev-frame buffer, the per-scanline diff, the bbox computation, the
SDL/0033 partial-flush dispatch path) but flips the default polarity
of SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PREVFRAME_DIFF from default-ON / strict-'0'-to-
disable to default-OFF / strict-'1'-to-enable. Matches the
wave-16+ convention used by SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_LFB,
DISPLAY_START_FIX, LFB_SENTINEL — all default-OFF / strict-'1'-
to-enable.

The mechanism stays in tree because LFB-flat-addressing modes (opt-in
via SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_LFB=1) might not have the per-rect
dispatch overhead — a stacked FORCE_LFB=1 + PREVFRAME_DIFF=1 is the
wave-17.6-release-iter PLAY3 experiment. After the iter measures we
either (a) cut the release with default-OFF and the mechanism becomes
a documented opt-in for users on hardware where it helps, or (b) the
LFB+partial combo wins and we re-flip to default-ON-when-LFB-engaged
in a future patch.

Two changes:

1. vendor/nxengine-evo/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp:
    polarity flipped. Strict
   '1' match enables (sets cached=0); anything else (unset, '0', any
   other value) leaves disabled (sets cached=1). Two LOG_INFO
   branches: ENABLED line cites the regression numbers; DISABLED line
   tells users how to opt in.

2. docs/BOOT.md (host repo, not vendor): moved the
   SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PREVFRAME_DIFF entry from
   'Compatibility / fallback options' to
   'Diagnostic / development options' and rewrote it as a default-OFF
   opt-in with the wave 17.4 / 17.5 regression numbers and the
   FORCE_LFB stacking note.

No other code changes. The wave-17.4 prev-frame buffer alloc /
memcmp / bbox / cache lifecycle / dtor / flushAll-reset paths all
stay — they just sit dormant under the default config.

Build verified locally (DJGPP cross-compile, 6,022,940 bytes,
strings grep confirms both branch messages embedded).
---
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp | 41 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 35 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index fa5216a..57fa3d3 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -1751,17 +1751,46 @@ void Renderer::_record_dirty_rect(int dst_x, int dst_y, int dst_w, int dst_h)
   _dirty_rects.push_back(r);
 }
 
-// DOS-PORT (patch 0082, Phase 9 wave 17.4): probe killswitch once on
-// first call. Strict "0" match disables the prev-frame diff path; all
-// other values keep the optimization on (default ON).
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0082, Phase 9 wave 17.4 / patch 0085, wave 17.6):
+// probe opt-in env var once on first call. Polarity flipped from
+// default-ON (wave 17.4 / 17.5) to default-OFF (wave 17.6) after both
+// partial-flush variants regressed on real HW (-7.1 fps wave 17.4
+// per-rect; -7.4 fps wave 17.5 bbox). Effective bandwidth measurement
+// showed partial path runs ~4× slower per byte than full flush
+// regardless of rect-vs-bbox structure — there's an unmodeled cost
+// in SDL3-DOS's per-rect dosmemput dispatch (or our diff CPU). Until
+// that cost is identified and modeled, the partial-flush path stays
+// opt-in via SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PREVFRAME_DIFF=1 (strict "1" match,
+// matching the wave-16+ default-OFF-via-strict-1 convention used by
+// SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_LFB / DISPLAY_START_FIX / LFB_SENTINEL).
+//
+// The mechanism stays in tree because LFB-flat-addressing modes
+// (opt-in via SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_LFB=1) might not have the
+// per-rect dispatch overhead — left as a release-iter PLAY3
+// experiment.
+//
+// See memory/wave_17_4_partial_flush_regression.md for the postmortem
+// + bandwidth measurements that drove this default flip.
 static bool _doskutsu_prev_frame_diff_is_disabled(int &cached)
 {
   if (cached < 0)
   {
     const char *e = std::getenv("SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PREVFRAME_DIFF");
-    cached = (e && e[0] == '0' && e[1] == 0) ? 1 : 0;
-    LOG_INFO("Renderer: prev-frame diff {} (set SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PREVFRAME_DIFF=0 to disable)",
-             cached ? "DISABLED (killswitch)" : "ENABLED (default)");
+    // Strict "1" match enables; everything else (unset, "0", any other
+    // value) leaves it disabled. Default OFF since wave 17.6.
+    const bool enabled = (e && e[0] == '1' && e[1] == 0);
+    cached = enabled ? 0 : 1;
+    if (enabled)
+    {
+      LOG_INFO("Renderer: prev-frame diff ENABLED via SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PREVFRAME_DIFF=1 "
+               "(experimental opt-in; default OFF after wave 17.5 measured -7.4 fps "
+               "regression on real HW)");
+    }
+    else
+    {
+      LOG_INFO("Renderer: prev-frame diff DISABLED (default since wave 17.6; "
+               "set SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PREVFRAME_DIFF=1 to opt in)");
+    }
   }
   return cached == 1;
 }
